MQTTREST API <pre><code>{
  "command": "set_impinjGen2X",
  "command_id": "auto-generated",
  "payload": {
    "fastID": {
      "enabled": true
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
  "fastID": {
    "enabled": true
  }
}
</code></pre>

MQTTREST API <pre><code>{
  "command": "set_impinjGen2X",
  "command_id": "auto-generated",
  "payload": {
    "fastID": {
      "enabled": false
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
  "fastID": {
    "enabled": false
  }
}
</code></pre> <p>TID Selector Values</p> <p>Supported values: <code>TID[0]</code>, <code>TID[1]</code>, <code>TID[2]</code>, <code>TID[3]</code>. When provided, only the specified TID word is embedded in the inventory response.</p>

MQTTREST API <pre><code>{
  "command": "get_impinjGen2X",
  "command_id": "auto-generated",
  "payload": {}
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>GET /cloud/impinjGen2X HTTP/1.1
Host: &lt;reader-ip&gt;
Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;
</code></pre> <p>cURL:</p> <pre><code>curl -X GET https://&lt;reader-ip&gt;/cloud/impinjGen2X \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;"
</code></pre>

MQTTREST API <p>All Gen2X commands are sent as JSON payloads to the MQTT command topic and responses are received on the response topic. Each command uses the same top-level structure:</p> <pre><code>{
  "command": "set_impinjGen2X",
  "command_id": "&lt;uuid&gt;",
  "payload": { ... }
}
</code></pre> <p>The <code>command_id</code> (UUID) correlates each response back to its original request.</p> <p>All Gen2X commands are sent as HTTP requests to a single endpoint on the reader. The REST API uses Bearer token authentication.</p> Method Endpoint Description GET <code>/cloud/impinjGen2X</code> Retrieve current Gen2X configuration PUT <code>/cloud/impinjGen2X</code> Set Gen2X configuration <p>Note</p> <p>The radio must be stopped before applying Gen2X configuration. Starting with Gen2X active while the radio is already running will return an error.</p>

MQTTREST API <pre><code>{
  "command": "set_impinjGen2X",
  "command_id": "auto-generated",
  "payload": {
    "tagProtect": {
      "action": "enableTagProtection",
      "password": "77777777",
      "tagID": "e2801191a5030069073b426d",
      "enableShortRange": true
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
  "tagProtect": {
    "action": "enableTagProtection",
    "password": "77777777",
    "tagID": "e2801191a5030069073b426d",
    "enableShortRange": true
  }
}
</code></pre> <p>Tip</p> <p>Short range is enabled by setting <code>enableShortRange: true</code> within the <code>enableTagProtection</code> action. It is not a separate command.</p>

MQTTREST API <pre><code>{
  "command": "start",
  "command_id": "auto-generated",
  "payload": {
    "applyImpinjGen2X": true
  }
}
</code></pre> <p>Use the start endpoint with the <code>applyImpinjGen2X</code> flag.</p> <p>Note</p> <p>The exact start endpoint depends on your reader's REST API version. Refer to your reader's full REST API documentation.</p> <p>Important</p> <p>The radio must be stopped before applying Gen2X configuration. Starting with Gen2X active while the radio is already running will return an error.</p>

MQTTREST API <pre><code>{
  "command": "set_impinjGen2X",
  "command_id": "same-as-request",
  "payload": {
    "message": "Success: Gen2X configured."
  },
  "response": "success"
}
</code></pre> <p>200 OK — Empty string response on success.</p> <p>Error Responses:</p> Status Description Example <code>422</code> Unprocessable Entity <code>{"message": "Invalid payload for set_impinjGen2X api"}</code> <code>500</code> Internal Server Error <code>{"code": 1, "message": "problem getting response for set_impinjGen2X"}</code>

